Freddie dashboard caveats: (1) anentrypoint-design source/dist pattern (2026-05-10) — no vendor dir in freddie. server.js always serves SDK from node_modules/anentrypoint-design/dist/. package.json pins "anentrypoint-design": "file:../anentrypoint-design" — npm install symlinks to live source. Rebuild dist locally via "node scripts/build.mjs" in C:/dev/anentrypoint-design (emits dist/247420.js ~441KB + 247420.css ~150ms). Skip rebuild before using new component → pageerror "component is not a function" kills app mount silently. (2) Live page rerender caveat — AppState.body caching breaks for live routes like #/chat where AppState is mutated mid-flight (SSE pushes). Fix: detect live routes in rerender(), recompute body via Promise. Any future live-streaming pages (cron output, traces) need same treatment. (3) libuv spawn caveat — spawning createDashboard() from exec:nodejs and keeping process alive triggers libuv UV_HANDLE_CLOSING crash on shutdown. Alternative: "node bin/freddie.js dashboard --port <port>". (4) anentrypoint-design theme token descendant selector fix (2026-05-04) — SDK CSS scopes light/dark vars under descendant selectors. Placing both class="ds-247420" and data-theme="dark" on same node breaks. Fix: ds-247420 on <html>, data-theme on <body>. Theme toggle writes to document.body.